cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG

The paper deals with modeling and analyzing visual designs, specifically magazine covers, using probabilistic generative models. This falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves analyzing visual media. The paper also uses computer vision techniques to analyze the images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the linguistic concepts associated with colors, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with retrieving relevant design examples and images. Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to learn color semantics, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
